Offer of Internship — AI Intern

Dear [Candidate Name],

We are pleased to offer you a fixed-term internship with Omninuera for the position of AI Intern on the terms set out below.

1. Position and Term
- Title: AI Intern.
- Term: Three (3) months (fixed-term internship), commencing on or about [Start Date] and ending approximately three months thereafter, unless earlier terminated in accordance with this letter.

2. Stipend
- You will receive a stipend of INR 10,000 (Indian Rupees Ten Thousand) per month, payable in arrears in accordance with Omninuera payroll schedules.
- The stipend is not a salary and does not establish an employment relationship that entitles you to employee benefits, except as may be required by applicable law.

3. Work Arrangement
- This role is completely remote. For jurisdictional purposes, you confirm that you are located in Bengaluru.
- Reporting: You will report to [Reporting Manager Name, Title].

4. Employment Relationship
- This offer is for an internship (stipend-based). Nothing in this letter creates a contract of employment for any guaranteed period, and you will not be entitled to employment benefits (such as paid leave, medical benefits, gratuity, provident fund, or other employee benefits) unless required by applicable law.
- The parties acknowledge that this is a fixed-term stipend engagement and not regular salaried employment.

5. Working Hours and Duties
- Expected weekly commitment: approximately 20–30 hours per week, with flexibility as this is a remote internship. Specific hours and deliverables will be agreed with your reporting manager.
- You are expected to perform duties assigned by Omninuera consistent with the role and to attend required meetings. No overtime compensation is provided beyond the stipend.

6. Confidentiality
- You will have access to confidential and proprietary information of Omninuera. During and after the term of the internship you must keep confidential all non-public information, trade secrets, technical and business information, client and supplier information, and other proprietary information belonging to Omninuera, except as required by law or with prior written permission.
- On termination or earlier request, you must return or destroy all confidential materials belonging to Omninuera.

7. Intellectual Property and Assignment
- You agree that all inventions, discoveries, developments, improvements, processes, software, works of authorship, designs, data, reports, analyses and other work product conceived, developed or reduced to practice by you, alone or with others, during the internship and related to Omninuera's business or created using Omninuera resources (collectively, Work Product), shall be the sole and exclusive property of Omninuera.
- To the extent permitted by applicable law, you hereby assign, and agree to execute any documents necessary to effect assignment of, all right, title and interest in and to such Work Product (including any moral rights). You agree to assist Omninuera (at Omninuera's expense) in obtaining and enforcing intellectual property protection.
- Note: LegalOrchestrator will perform a legal compliance review of the confidentiality and IP clauses. These clauses must not be altered until LegalOrchestrator's review is completed.

8. Background Checks
- This offer is conditional upon Omninuera receiving satisfactory results from any background checks or verifications that Omninuera deems appropriate (education, employment, criminal background, or other checks where permitted). If a background check is unsatisfactory, Omninuera may withdraw or terminate the offer.

9. Termination
- Termination for convenience: Either party may terminate this internship for convenience by providing seven (7) calendar days' prior written notice to the other party.
- Termination for cause: Omninuera may terminate the internship immediately for cause, including material breach of this agreement, misconduct, theft, fraud, violation of Omninuera policies, unauthorized disclosure of confidential information, or other serious misconduct. In the event of termination for cause, Omninuera may cease stipend payments except to the extent required by applicable law for services already rendered.
- On termination, you must return all Omninuera property and confidential materials.

10. Taxes
- The stipend is subject to applicable taxes and statutory deductions as required by law. You are responsible for your personal tax obligations arising from the stipend unless Omninuera is legally required to withhold taxes under applicable law. Where required by law, Omninuera may withhold taxes at source.

11. Compliance with Policies
- During the internship you must comply with Omninuera policies, guidelines, and any reasonable direction from your reporting manager.

12. Governing Law and Jurisdiction
- This letter and the internship shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of India. The courts located in Bengaluru, State of Karnataka, shall have exclusive jurisdiction over any disputes arising out of or in connection with this internship.

13. Acceptance
- To accept this offer, please sign and date below and return a scanned copy of this letter by the date indicated by Omninuera (or within a reasonable period). This offer will lapse if not accepted within a reasonable time.

14. Additional Terms
- Any modification to the confidentiality, IP assignment, or other legal clauses should not be made until LegalOrchestrator completes its legal review. Do not alter these clauses without LegalOrchestrator's written confirmation.

Sincerely,

For Omninuera

